[We have received additional news reports that I have not posted since they
did not shed much light on the source of the outbreak and did not report
new cases. To summarize reports from various French and Spanish
newspapers, the strain of _Listeria_ isolated from Sapar food products pork
tongue was reported to be different from the strain responsible for the
outbreak. The Sapar plant mysteriously burned two days after this strain
discrepancy was reported, so records have been destroyed. Sapar pork
tongue was initially suspected because of a report from Austrian customs
officials that Sapar pork tongue products had unacceptable levels of
_Listeria_ contamination. Most EU countries have recalled Sapar products at
this point in time. Pork tongue is still suspected since 55% of infected
persons have reported consuming this product. Eleven suppliers are under
investigation. - Mod.ES
